if you know me, you know I’m all about balance. Mom’s ask me all the time, how do you do it all?! Here’s what works for me when it comes to self-care.

Prioritization: every mom out there should know that it’s super important to prioritize self-care. I mean, taking care of yourself is not selfish—it’s necessary!
 
Boundaries: listen up! Setting boundaries is key when it comes to making time for self-care. You gotta communicate + establish clear boundaries with your family and loved ones. Let them know that you need dedicated time to focus on your own needs and recharge!

Guilt-free: moms, we all know that guilt can creep in when you try to take time for yourself. But here’s the thing: you deserve self-care, and you shouldn’t feel guilty about it! Embrace the idea that self-care is not only beneficial for you but also for your family.

embracing these secrets, create a healthier + more balanced lifestyle that includes self-care practices. 

Trust me, you’ll be happier, more energized, and better equipped to handle the demands of #motherhood. You got this! 🫶🏻

BIG NEWS! Starting June 19, I’ll be hosting NBC Miami’s new lifestyle and entertainment show, South Florida Live! 

Picture this: trendy hotspots, A-list events that make South Florida the ultimate playground, red carpet affairs to jaw-dropping fashion shows, best restaurants, family friendly things to do and all your beauty tips and tricks - I’m bringing you the inside scoop on all things lifestyle and entertainment. 

For those of you who have watched my career as a Traffic Anchor grow, thank you. Your countless messages, advice, comments have built me up and helped me get to where I am now. So many of you have been rooting for me to push for the next big thing and hosting South Florida Live is it!

I cannot wait to show off South Florida, my home, and to present it to you like never before. So, join me every weekday at 12:30p & let’s show off to the world what we already know: there is no place like South Florida!

Out of the Office; please leave a message 💌
.
.
Captained a boat to #HvarIsland today with 7 of my girlfriends and it was the best decision. Hvar is known as the party island of Croatia because of all the bars and restaurants - it really was a vibe. I loved how it’s still locally visited (by Europeans) and not as busy as Ibiza. 
.
.
.
.
From Hvar, we took our boat to another island with a bunch of bits from yacht week and that was a blast. There were so many people rent yachts from around the world, young and old, all equally looking to have a good time. 
.
.
.
They have the cutest beach bar there, with the clearest water and amazing restaurants. We heard the Tuna was the the thing to order but we when we went to the restaurant it wasn’t on the menu! Apparently, it’s a non-menu menu item 😂 
.
.
.
The tuna tartar, tuna ceviche + and tuna seared from ToTo’s was fab 😚 oh and the French Fries were a great little treat too. 
Set: @tanyataylor 
Tan: @liquidgoldmiami 
.
.
.

📍 Dubrovnik, Croatia
.
.
I’ve never seen #GameofThrones before but after walking the medieval city walls, I’m inspired. Also, I saw and heard the stories about the infamous Season 5 “Walk of Shame” scene that took place on the Jesuit Staircase that descends from Gundulić Square to St. Ignatius Church… this show seems wild. 
.
.
.
Beyond the show, the city is really beautiful, with so many hidden alleys and flights of stairs. It’s so easy to get lost! 
.
.
.
Although I thought prices were a little expensive for a city still growing, the culture was still very much alive. I did think it would be difficult to travel with small kids because of so many stairs, but definitely a great couples or friend destination. Oh, and the waiters get overwhelmed with complicated orders, so keep it easy 😅 
.
.
.
If you’re planning a trip! Buy the city pass, it gets you into the city walls, museums + galleries all for the same price as one ticket for the walls. Take the cable car to the top for great views on the old town (slide 8 + 9). The city is known for oyster farms, so make sure to order a few! And the red wine + #CocaCola is a little treat our Croatian family who gave us a cooking lesson taught us! More to come on that 😋 
.
.
9/10 experience in #Dubrovnik 

#traveltips #travelguide #thingstodoineurope #croatia #travelwithme #cruisedestinations #cruisinglife

📍Boka Bay, Montenegro 🇲🇪 
.
.
Feeling so lucky to explore this country for the first time with my girlfriends. I love renting a captained catamaran when exploring a new city, so that’s exactly what we did here!
.
.
We left from the Old Town Kotor and took about an hour car ride to Porto Montenegro - it’s one of the most prestigious marinas on the #AdriaticSea. It’s easy to tell too with all the super yachts docked!
.
.
.
I highly recommend an excursion that includes unlimited snacks + (adult bevs) because it makes us that much more fun ✨ 
.
.
.
There were so many cute coastal towns we saw and we learned that event though Casino Royale our Montenegro on the map, none of it was actually filmed there 😂 
.
.
. 
Jumping in the bay was definitely a peak and I highly recommend this destination for a visit. Next time I want to leave room for all the fab beach clubs - I hear there amazing - mostly because it’s still it’s just vacationed by Europeans 😚 
.
.

heading back to the Hamptons in a few weeks + can’t wait to visit some of my favorite spots 🏡 

Where are some of your favorite places to go?

taking my son to my favorite summer hideaway was my favorite highlight this year 🫶🏻 @loulou_la_plage at the Maidstone was just one of the many beautiful spots that makes the Hamptons the Hamptons 🤍

We explored East Hampton, which I highly recommend. It has some of the best window shopping out East. It’s so wild for me to witness the glow up eastern Long Island has had. I grew up taking old MTK Hwy (yes, the bumpy roads) to Montauk every weekend + it was always an escape from the busy city life. Now, the city has come arrived in a place that used to be so quiet! It is truly beautiful no matter when you come. If you ever visit - enjoy the gorgeous beaches, the homegrown Long Island accents + the people the make this island thrive 🙌🏻

Disney really is magical 💌

some of my favorite moments from the weekend 🪄 I can’t believe our little boy is two + staying on Disney property really was the best way to introduce our little one to the charm 🤍

I love to travel, but traveling with kids, I’ve learned is a whole other adventure. Whenever we bring our baby along for the ride, doing as much as possible at one place is key. If you’re planning a trip, make sure you love the place you choose for the vacation because it’ll make your lives so much easier! We opted to skip the Disney parks + do Breakfast with Mickey, Minnie + Goofy at our hotel instead. It was so sweet to see preston have so much one on one time with all the characters 🥹

the sunsets, scavenger hunts, water park, slides + so many treats added to all the fun. By the way, I always check to see if hotels offer resident rates + this one was one of them @fsorlando! we always ask for an extra fridge in our room and stop by the store to grab milk + snacks so we’re not always having to leave property! I’m no expert in traveling with kiddies but these are some of the tricks I’ve found so helpful for us ✨

Take a small eyeshadow brush + gently apply a bit of a contour powder or cream underneath the center of your bottom lip to create the illusion that the lip is full + casting a shadow. 

Be sure to blend the contour so it’s subtle + not overdone.

Start with lip primer, I like to line with a dark liner + mix with a lighter lipstick color + add a dot of gloss to the bottom for a 3D pop ✨

My skin has been so dry this pregnancy + I’m missing that glow I had with my first!

Here’s some food for thought from @drrobertadelcampo!

1. It is common to notice dry, sensitive skin when pregnant so it is important to follow these steps. Wash with a soap free gentle cleaner. Pat the skin dry to leave a light layer on water on the skin. Apply a hyaluronic acid serum to increase moisture in the skin. Layer with a cream to seal the moisture in the skin.

2. Hormonal acne can occur. If so it’s important to avoid traditional acne products which include benzoyl peroxide, retinols and salicylic acid. Rather a gentle cleaner and a sulfur based product is a better option. 

3. Sun protection with a and then I’ll be sunblock is a must. When pregnant, the skin can become a bit more sensitive increasing the risk of burning. Further pigmentation, such as cholasma (the mask of pregnancy) is prevalent and sun protection will help to minimize flaring.

Maternity Leave starts now 🫶🏻
9 months with the girls —-> 9 months with Preston

What a wild ride it’s been. I feel so fortunate to have been able to work through (almost) 38 weeks of a twin pregnancy. When I first found out I was having twins, my doctor told me I’d likely be on bed rest at 26 weeks. In my mind that wasn’t a choice. 

It hasn’t been easy + many days I just wanted to say ‘I can’t do it today’ - but I showed up. Why? Truthfully, I love what I do. I’m passionate about telling stories, sharing what’s happening throughout south Florida + having fun while hosting and emceeing. 

I also do it for me. I like a challenge, I love to work + I’ve never been one to take the easy way out. With that said - I’ll be back 🫶🏻 

I’ve had so many question asking about my return and I’ll be back this summer after a very generous maternity leave. 

It’s been so fun launching South Florida live, being the host + showing you all the cool, glamours + fulfilling things there is to do in our home. 

In the meantime, keep up with me + my family of FIVE here. Don’t be surprised if you see the girls + son on air once they arrive. 

To all my working moms out there who want to have their cake + eat it too - you got this 🤍

the girls are almost here 🫶🏻

Here’s a glimpse of our nursery 🤍 

I wanted to make this a room that’s calm, soft + cozy. r restoration hardware is our go to furniture store, which really helped when we pieced together our girls nursery. we used Preston’s crib, dresser + rocker. The tufted bed was in our guest room. we discovered this beautiful 3D art from the Baby & Child section + completed the room with @houseofnoa_ little nomad play mat instead of a rug. 

one of my dearest friends got preston @littlegiraffeislove + I wanted the same for my girls. all the lovies, blankets + pillows are so soft. 

You’ll notice we only have one crib is the room. It’s recommended to keep the twins together for their bond + it’s safe for them to sleep together until they start to crawl. I love the idea of them sharing this safe place. I feel like this room has taken forever to complete + it’s so wild my twins will call this theirs this week. I had a c-section with Preston + we’ll do a repeat this time around. Peep delivery date at the end of my reel 🫶🏻
